org.beiter.michael.eaudit4j.common.impl

Class ExtendedAuditEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.beiter.michael.eaudit4j.common.impl.AuditEvent
      • org.beiter.michael.eaudit4j.common.impl.ExtendedAuditEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Event, ExtendedEvent

    public class ExtendedAuditEvent
extends AuditEvent
implements ExtendedEvent
    This class implements an ExtendedEvent. In addition to the basic properties defined in Event, it also implements the extended (frequently used) audit event properties defined in ExtendedEvent.

      • ExtendedAuditEvent

        public ExtendedAuditEvent(CommonProperties properties,
                          Field... fields)
        Create a new (extended) audit event.

        Use this constructor in case you want to create an event that is pre-populated with the provided fields.

        You may still use the setters to add additional fields.

        Note that this constructor creates defensive copies of the data in the provided fields. You need to explicitly clear the fields provided to this constructor if they contain confidential information that you wish to destroy.

        Parameters:
        properties - The configuration properties to be used by this event instance
        fields - The fields to set
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - When value is null

    • Method Detail

      • setEventType

        public final String setEventType(char[] value)
        This method sets a field that represents an event type.

        This is a convenience method if applications want to use this field, and also want to use the standard field name for it. If you want to set a different field name for this field, you should use the generic Event.setField(Field) method.

        The name of the field will be determined by the implementation of this interface.

        Implementations of this method should create a defensive copy of the provided audit data (the char[] value), and stores the copy in the event. You need to explicitly clear the data provided to this method if it contains confidential information that you wish to destroy.

        The field is named according to the well-known field names defined in CommonProperties as provided at creation of this object, the value for the field is taken from the provided parameter.

        Note that the value of the provided char is encoded using the charset specified in CommonProperties.getEncoding()

        Specified by:
        setEventType in interface ExtendedEvent
        Parameters:
        value - The value of the field to set
        Returns:
        The name of the field that was added to the event
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - When value is null

      • toJson

        public final char[] toJson()
        Create a JSON serialized representation of the event using String encoding specified in CommonProperties.getEncoding(). This JSON representation in particular contains all fields that are registered with the event.

        The event is serialized into a default format, the version of which can be obtained with the Event.getRecordFormatVersion() method.

        Specified by:
        toJson in interface ExtendedEvent
        Returns:
        A JSON representation of the event.
